import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['id'] = pd.to_datetime(data['id'], format='%Y%m%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['id'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='id')
    plt.plot(data['id'], data['rate'])
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of unemployment rate?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

    ax.set_xlabel('Unemployment Rate')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of unemployment rate across different regions?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.style.use('ggplot')
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    plt.bar(data['id'], data['rate'], color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axhline(y=data['rate'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average Rate')
    plt.xlabel('Region ID')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.title('What is the average unemployment rate for each region?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

unemployment_data = pd.read_csv('unemployment.tsv', delimiter='\t')
chart = plot(unemployment_data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    age_groups = pd.cut(data['id'], bins=np.arange(1000, 73000, 5000))
    data['age_groups'] = age_groups
    grouped_data = data.groupby('age_groups')['rate'].agg(['mean', 'count'])
    ax = grouped_data.plot(kind='bar', y='mean', legend=False)
    ax.set_xlabel('Age Groups')
    ax.set_ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of unemployment rate for each age group?')
    for i, v in enumerate(grouped_data['mean']):
        ax.text(i, v, str(round(v, 3)), ha='center', va='bottom')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
